    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The _easy fix_ seems to replace in generic.py:\n[`**other._construct_axes_dict()`](https://github.com/pydata/pandas/blob/master/pandas/core/generic.py#L4156) by `**self._construct_axes_dict(**other._construct_axes_dict(axes=['columns']))`\nand\n[`**self._construct_axes_dict()`](https://github.com/pydata/pandas/blob/master/pandas/core/generic.py#L4165) by `**other._construct_axes_dict(**self._construct_axes_dict(axes=['columns']))`\n\nHowever, looking at the code I see another issue: though the documentation mentions as possible values for broadcast_axis: {0, 1, ‘index’, ‘columns’}, in reality only `broadcast_axis == 1` has been implemented!\n\nUnfortunately, I don't have the time now to implement that myself. I hope someone else will take this up...\n"
